VALUES (1010, 'Sprinkle 1 cup almonds into bottom of a well-greased       and floured 10"\000a  tube pan; set aside. Combine cake mix,     pudding mix, eggs, oil, water,\000a  amaretto, and almond        extract in a mixing bowl; beat on low speed of\000a  an\000a         electric mixer til dry ingredients are moistened.          Increase\000a  speed to medium, and beat 4 minutes. Stir in      remaining 1/2 cup\000a  almonds. Pour batter into prepared       tube pan. Bake at 325~ for 1 hour\000a  or til a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool cake in pan\000a    10-15 minutes; remove from pan, and cool completely.       Combine sugar,\000a  water, and butter in a small saucepan;      bring to a boil. Reduce heat to\000a  medium and gently boil     4-5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until sugar\000a  dissolves. Remove from heat, and cool 15 minutes. Stir\000a  in amaretto and almond extract. Punch holes in top of      cake with a\000a  wooden pick; slowly spoon glaze on top of cake, allowing glaze to absorb in\000a  cake.\000a  Posted to MC-Recipe Digest V1 #263\000a  \000a  Date: Sun, 27 Oct 1996 20:04:57 +0000\000a  \000a  From: Cheryl Gimenez &lt;clgimenez@earthlink.net&gt;', 'Amaretto Cake', 1);
